    "The buzz around generative AI has skyrocketed, with ChatGPT expanding to have over 100 million users 3.",
    "Over the past year, many have shown excitement for potential generative AI applications to healthcare.",
    "LLMs have already been used to pass the United States Medical Licensing Examination 4, write research articles 5, and interpret electronic medical record data 6.",
    "This last use case is perhaps closest to the bedside.",
    "Generative AI models trained on EMR data, such as notes, lab values, and billing codes, hold the promise of better predictive performance, simpler model development (with less labeled data required) and cheaper model deployment 7."
